<chapter id="Third_Party_Transfer"> 
<title>Third Party Transfer</title>

<section condition="TITLE=Cash Services: Third Party Transfer;PERM=ft_tpt_access;ACCESS=TPT_01" id="TPT" role="TOPIC">
    <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Third_Party_Transfer"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/></title>

    <para role="TEXT">A <guimenuitem>Third Party Transfer</guimenuitem> is
    funds transfer to the beneficiary account of another customer in the same
    bank. This system allows for instant fund transfers. For example, the
    funds transfer will be credited to the beneficiary account in a few
    seconds.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click <guimenuitem>Fund Transfers</guimenuitem> from
    <guimenuitem>Cash Services</guimenuitem> from the main menu (horizontal
    drop-down menu on the top) and then, from the left vertical menu, click
    <guimenuitem>Third Party Transfer</guimenuitem> from
    <guimenuitem>Initiation</guimenuitem>. The Create a Third Party Transfer
    screen appears.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Create a Third Party Transfer</title>

      <para role="TEXT">The screen presents details and input fields for:
      General Details, Transfer To Details, Transaction Details, Beneficiary
      Notification, and Transaction Remarks. Enter details for the various
      sections and click the appropriate action buttons on the screen.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Note: Third Party Transfer is also available from the
      Initiation menu.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Refer the the tables in the following subsections for
      information on the various sections and the action buttons on the
      screen.</para>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Create a Third Party Transfer - General Details</title>

        <para role="TEXT">The following table provides details for this section:</para>

        <informaltable role="TEXT">
          <tgroup cols="3">
